            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Hd1e108">Rubrica 10</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De confidentia: credulitate et credulis atque incredulis</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>
      ¶ De confidentia credulitate 
               cre<lb ed="#V" n="76" break="no"/>dulis atque incredulis. Rubrica. 10
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="77"/><ref>ISocrates in 
               exorta<lb ed="#V" n="78" break="no"/>tionibus:
      <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e129">Expedire putes non esse 
               creden<lb ed="#V" n="80" break="no"/>dum temerariis prout credendum probis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e135">
               <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>
               ¶ <ref>Aristoteles rethoricorum. lib. i. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e139">
               Mode<lb ed="#V" n="82" break="no"/>stis credimus magis et scelerius</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e146"> /
      <ref>Lib. 2. c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e148">Iuuenes sunt faciles creditiui: propterea
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>quod nondum in multis decepti sunt. Iuuenes
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>facile seducibiles sunt: sperant enim facile. 
               Se<lb ed="#V" n="86" break="no"/>nes increduli sunt: propter experientiam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e160">
               <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>
               ¶ <ref>Iesus filius sirach in eccl. c. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e164">Non 
               cre<lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>das inimico tuo in eternum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e170"> /
      <ref>c. 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e172">Qui 
               cre<lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>dit cito leuis est corde: et minorabitur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>Non omni verbo credas.<!--96.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="35-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e186">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
               ¶ <ref>Tullius retho. artis vereris li. i. c. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e190">
               Sum<lb ed="#V" n="2" break="no"/>ma amentia est in eorum fide spem habere 
               quo<lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>rum perfidia deceptus sis multotiens.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e198"> /
      <ref>Lib. 2
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>c. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e200">Fidentia est per quam magnis et 
               hone<lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>stis rebus: multum ipse animus in se fiducia
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>certa cum spe collocauit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e210">
               <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>
               ¶ <ref>Quidius epistolarum. epi 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e214">Credulitas
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>damno solet esse puellis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e221"> /
      <ref>Idem de arte 
               aman<lb ed="#V" n="9" break="no"/>di li. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e223">Nec ciro credideris: quantum cito
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>credere ledat. Exemplum nobis non leue 
               pro<lb ed="#V" n="11" break="no"/>crus erit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e233">
      <ref>Idem de tristibus li. 4. e. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e235">Crede quod est et vis: ac desine tuta vereri.
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>Deque fide certa: sit tibi certa fides.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e243">
               <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
               <ref>Seneca declam. li. 5. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e247">Nemo facile 
               cre<lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>dit: quo credito sit dolendum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e253"> /
      <ref>Idem in 
               pro<lb ed="#V" n="16" break="no"/>uerb.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e255">Utrumque vitium est: et omnibus credere et nulli.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e261">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
               ¶ <ref>Ioannes apostolus et euange. in epistola vnica. c. 4.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e265">Nolite credere omni spiritui: sed probate 
               spiri<lb ed="#V" n="19" break="no"/>tus si ex deo sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e273">
               <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>
               ¶ <ref>Marcialis cocus li. vndique. suscepto. c. 5.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e277">Omnibus et nulli te credere vitium est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e284">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
               ¶ <ref>Uegetius de re mili. li. 3. ti. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e288">Frequentius
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>conuentionum pacisque simulatio credulis 
               no<lb ed="#V" n="24" break="no"/>cuere quam arma.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e296">
               <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>
               ¶ <ref>Auctor lib. de for. honeste vite. ca. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e300">
               Ru<lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>moribus criminum et suspitionibus minime
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>sis credulus: sed potius malignis qui per 
               spe<lb ed="#V" n="28" break="no"/>ciem simplicitatis ad nocendum aliquibus 
               sub<lb ed="#V" n="29" break="no"/>repunt oppositi simus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e312">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
               ¶ <ref>Ambrosius de officiis li. i. c. 31.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e316">
               Unusquis<lb ed="#V" n="31" break="no"/>que bene volentis se magis quam sapientis credit
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>consilio</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e324"> /
      <ref>Libro. 2. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e326">Promptius nos 
               iu<lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>sto viro quam prudenti committimus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e332">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
               ¶ <ref>Fulgentius li. 3. et fi. fabula. 15.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e336">
               Creduli<lb ed="#V" n="35" break="no"/>tas semper deceptionum mater est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e342">
               <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>
               ¶ <ref>Cato. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e346">Nil temere credideris.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e351"> /
      <ref>Ca. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e353">Noli tu quedam referenti credere semper.
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>Exigua est tribuenda fides: quia multi 
               mul<lb ed="#V" n="39" break="no"/>ta loquuntur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e363">
               <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>
               ¶ <ref>Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 3. e. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e367">Illi credere
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>debetis quem vestris vtilitatibus arridem 
               co<lb ed="#V" n="42" break="no"/>gnoscitis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e375">
               <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>
               ¶ <ref>Uersificator fabularum esopi. fab. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e379">Non
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>satis est tutum mellitis credere verbis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Ex hoc melle: solet pestis amara sequi.<!--96.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e391">
               <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>
               ¶ <ref>Fabula. 25.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e395">Tempore non omni: non omnibus omnia 
               cre<lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>das. Qui misere credit: creditur esse miser.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e401">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>
               ¶ <ref>Fabula 31.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e405">Qui me lesit: idem ledet si 
               lede<lb ed="#V" n="49" break="no"/>re posset. Expedit insido: non interare fidem.
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>Que dedit infidus mella venena puto.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e413">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
               ¶ <ref>Ualdo fabula. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e417">Nec confidatis secreta
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>nec his detegatis. Cum quibus egistis: 
               pu<lb ed="#V" n="53" break="no"/>gne discrimina tristis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e426"> ¶
      <ref>Fabula. 26</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e428">Nulla fidis hosti tibi sit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>Prorsus et hostilis: tibi sit suasio vilis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e436">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>
               ¶ <ref>Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria: parte
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>i. c. 20.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e440">Credulitas sestina nocet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-d1e446">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
               ¶ <ref>Prouerb. vulgar:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d26532-Qd1e450">Et passiu non cre al zuno
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>Tuto crere noe sauere.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
